title: async_graphql::DataLoader code generation via declarative and attribute macros causes compiler bug

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
### Code Unable to produce limited code example as reducing the number of models being operated on makes the compiler bug go away. Codebase is sensitive, please reach out about repository access if interested ```Rust #[cfg(test)] mod test { use async_graphql::*; use hedgehog_rust_server::entities::{ 110 models }; use hedgehog_rust_server::impl_data_loaders; use hedgehog_rust_server::impl_graphql_queries; #[test] #[ignore] pub fn code_gen() -> Result<()> { trace_macros!(true); impl_graphql_queries! { 550 model connections } impl_data_loaders! { 550 model connections } Ok(()) } } ``` ### Meta Running `rust:1.64-slim-bullseye` Docker container on Mac M1 ``` rustc 1.64.0 (a55dd71d5 2022-09-19) binary: rustc
